pulltitle: Embed dashboards, Firebase bug, Docs
pullsbody:
Sorry. This is three small issues in one PR.
1. in `app/components/mentions.jsx` the app was failing because there wasn't a `this.state.handle` was undefined when calling `.toLowerCase()`. I wrapped this in an if statement so I could work on adding the dashboards
2. I added a dashboards route which embeds metrics.w.o in an iframe
3. I got caught out by the need to add the route to `server.js`, so I added a note about this to the README
pull_repo_desc: Source behind MoFo's project tracking site

pulltitle: Swapping gulp-express to gulp-live-server
pullsbody:
I'm out of my depth here working on gulp and server setup type things, but this works :wink: 

**Why?**

I couldn't get the server to run locally ( #65 ) in my dev environment. I believe @simonwex was seeing the same issue. 

**What?**
- I replaced `gulp-express` with `gulp-live-server` because that was what `gulp-express` [recommends](https://github.com/gimm/gulp-express). 
- This showed me errors which allowed me to get the app running (needed a Firebase key)
- It also started the server! (Even after fixing the Firebase error, I couldn't get `gulp-express` to work again)
- So, if people who know more about these things than me are happy, this seems to work

**Also**
- Just to check. Should I be committing those two build files?
pull_repo_desc: Source behind MoFo's project tracking site

pulltitle: Surface more roles than just owner
pullsbody:
- two-column layout for now, although ugly
- uses a webhook to get notified of new issues, and uses firebase to keep data about who'se been assigned what roles in which issue (will be used in dashboard as well) (code reused from plzkthx)
- uses github API to populate autocompletes in the 'add' view so that we prompt for decision-maker and driver explicitly.
- minor layout tweaks
- parse markdown in issue bodies.

The react-select.css should be loaded from the `node_modules/react-select/dist/default.css` file instead, but I couldn't figure out how to get that file embedded.
pull_repo_desc: Source behind MoFo's project tracking site
